      • execAt

        public void execAt(long id,
                   SerializableConsumer<V> op)
        Execute the specified operation with the corresponding value of the specified id.
        • If the entry is stored at local, the operation is executed sequentially.
        • If the entry is stored at a remote place, the operation is asynchronously executed on the remote place

        In the remote case, this method returns immediately. Actual completion of the operation can only be guaranteed if this method's enclosing Constructs.finish(apgas.Job) has returned.

        Parameters:
        id - a Long type value.
        op - the operation.

      • writeReplace

        public Object writeReplace()
                    throws ObjectStreamException
        Description copied from interface: DistributedCollection
        Method used to create an object which will be transferred to a remote place.

        This method is present in interface DistributedCollection to force the implementation in implementing classes. Implementation should return a LazyObjectReference instance capable of initializing the local handle of the implementing class on the remote place

        Specified by:

        Overrides:
